      • writeKey

        public abstract int writeKey​(int keyAlgorithmType,
                             int keyType,
                             int srcKeyIndex,
                             int destKeyIndex,
                             byte[] key,
                             int checkMode,
                             byte[] checkValue)
        Write the terminal secure key
        Parameters:
        keyAlgorithmType - key algorithm type form PINPadConstants.KEY_ALGORITHM_TYPE_DES_1 to PINPadConstants.KEY_ALGORITHM_TYPE_AES_256
        keyType - the write key type form PINPadConstants.KEY_TYPE_TLK to PINPadConstants.KEY_TYPE_TIK
        srcKeyIndex - source key index
        destKeyIndex - dest key index
        key - key data
        checkMode - the mode of the check key. PINPadConstants.CHECK_VALUE_MODE_NULL to PINPadConstants.CHECK_VALUE_MODE_AES_0
        checkValue - the check value when checkMode is PINPadConstants.CHECK_VALUE_MODE_NULL, the checkValue is null
        Returns:
        Returns 0 as success, others as errors

                                           int tikIndex,
                                           int deriveType,
                                           int usage,
                                           byte[] data)
        encrypt data by dukpt key
        Parameters:
        keyAlgorithmType - key algorithm type form PINPadConstants.KEY_ALGORITHM_TYPE_DES_1 to PINPadConstants.KEY_ALGORITHM_TYPE_AES_256
        tikIndex - TIK index PINPadConstants.KEY_TYPE_TIK
        deriveType - derive type only aes dukpt key need to use PINPadConstants.DUKPT_AES_DERIVE_KEY_TYPE_DES2 to PINPadConstants.DUKPT_AES_DERIVE_KEY_TYPE_AES256
        usage - PINPadConstants.DUKPT_AES_USAGE_Key_Encryption_Key to PINPadConstants.DUKPT_AES_USAGE_Key_Derivation_Initial_Key or PINPadConstants.DUKPT_DES_USAGE_PIN_Encryption to PINPadConstants.DUKPT_DES_USAGE_Data_Encryption_encrypt
        data - Data that requires encryption
        Returns:
        Returns 0 as success, others as errors

      • getCheckValue

        public abstract byte[] getCheckValue​(int keyAlgorithmType,
                                     int keyType,
                                     int keyIndex)
        Obtain the KCV value of the key for key verification by both sides of the conversation, encrypt a piece of data with the specified key and the algorithm, and return part of the data ciphertext.
        Parameters:
        keyAlgorithmType - key algorithm type form PINPadConstants.KEY_ALGORITHM_TYPE_DES_1 to PINPadConstants.KEY_ALGORITHM_TYPE_AES_256
        keyType - key type form PINPadConstants.KEY_TYPE_TLK to PINPadConstants.KEY_TYPE_TIK
        keyIndex - key index
        Returns:
        part of the data ciphertext. The key performs DES encryption on 0 of 8 bytes, and the first 4 bytes of the generated ciphertext are KCV. or The key uses this key to perform AES encryption on 0 of 16 bytes, and the first 4 bytes of the generated ciphertext are KCV.

      • enterPinInputMode

        public abstract int enterPinInputMode​(int keyAlgorithmType,
                                      boolean isDukptKey,
                                      int keyIndex,
                                      int calcMode,
                                      int minInputLen,
                                      int maxInputLen,
                                      boolean enableByPass,
                                      int timeout)
        Enter password input mode, which is required for customizing the password keyboard，At the end, exitPinInputMode() needs to be called, otherwise the touch screen will not be usable
        Parameters:
        keyAlgorithmType - key algorithm type form PINPadConstants.KEY_ALGORITHM_TYPE_DES_1 to PINPadConstants.KEY_ALGORITHM_TYPE_AES_256
        isDukptKey - Is it a dukpt secret key
        keyIndex - key index
        calcMode - pinBlock mode PINPadConstants.PINBLOCK_MODE_ISO_9564_0 to PINPadConstants.PINBLOCK_MODE_ISO_9564_4
        minInputLen - min input password len
        maxInputLen - max input password len
        enableByPass - enable to pass input password
        timeout - timeout (millisecond)
        Returns:
        Returns 0 as success, others as errors

      • exitPinInputMode

        public abstract int exitPinInputMode()
        Exit the password input mode, which is required for customizing the password keyboard. If you do not exit, the touch screen will not be able to be used
        Returns:
        Returns 0 as success, others as errors
